sa:

  Base64 is used in the Basic → development/web/HTTP authentication scheme to transmit user-id/password pairs (see → development/web/RFC#rfc-7617[RFC-7617]).

  Base64 is described in → development/web/RFC#rfc-4648[RFC 4648]

  → development/Base64/Encoding-and-decoding-base-64-with-cpp

  The Python module `→ development/languages/Python/standard-library/binascii` has the two functions
  → development/languages/Python/standard-library/binascii#py-binascii-base64[`b2a_base64` and `a2b_base64`].

  On a → Windows command line, → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/certutil_exe/encode-decode[`certutil -decode`] and `certutil -decode` provide a possibility to
  encode/decode a file in base 64 if no tool can be installed.
  -
  On Linux, there is the `→ Linux/shell/commands/base64` utility.
 
 `→ development/languages/Java/classes/java/util/Base64`

  The Perl module `→ development/languages/Perl/modules/MIME/Base64`

  → development/web/Multipurpose-Internet-Mail-Extensions

  Using → development/web/HTML/tags/img/data-uri[data URIs] (`<img src="data:…, ">`) in → development/web/HTML[HTML] to embed (usually → development/Data/binary) data (encoded in Base64) within
  the HTML document itself.

